DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
);
 
Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->add( t=>'Real' );

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$y0 = random(10,35,1);
$whichtrig = random(0,1,1);
if ( $whichtrig ) { 
    $g = '\sin';
    $ans = "2*pi*cos(2*pi*t)";
    $sol = "2\pi\cos(2\pi t)";
} else {
    $g = '\cos';
    $ans = "-2*pi*sin(2*pi*t)";
    $sol = "-2\pi\sin(2\pi t)";
}

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

A boat at anchor is bobbing up and down in the sea. The vertical
distance, \( y \), in feet, between the sea floor and
the boat is given as a function of time, \( t \), in minutes, by
\( y = $y0 + $g(2\pi t) \) ft.
$PAR
Find the vertical velocity,  \( v \), of the boat at time  \( t \).
$BR
\( v = \) \{ ans_rule(65) \} ft/min

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;


ANS(Compute( $ans )->cmp() );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

The velocity is \( v(t) = {dy\over dt} \), so
\[ v(t) = $sol \hbox{\rm\ ft/min}. \]

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


COMMENT('MathObject version');
ENDDOCUMENT();
